				**Pi hole Adblocker**

The purpose of this mini project is to be able to use virtual machine to block ads across the entire network. ![][image1]  
Tools used:

- Virtualbox: running Ubuntu-server   
- Pihole: The tool to block ads

	First of all, Installation of ubuntu server and setting up a static ip for it. Which can be done by going into /etc/netplan/ and edit the file to a static ip and gateway.  
![][image2]![][image3]

Once done, the ip should be 192.168.1.20/24, which the screenshot shows. After we install Pihole using curl \-sSL [https://install.pi-hole.net](https://install.pi-hole.net) | bash.![][image4]  
Choose your dns and I also enabled “Show everything” for better learning, debugging and security analysis.  
![][image5]  
Once done this should show, the address of the web interface and the password to login. 

After this, we need to configure the dns server to use our Pihole static ip to be the actual dns server. Which should be in the LAN section of the router, and DHCP configuration. ![][image6]

After applying the change, Turn off then on for the wifi, and the Pihole adblocker are active. ![][image7]![][image8]
